The paper focuses on the challenges faced by blind people in using smartphones, which is related to human-computer interaction (HCI) and accessibility. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing data from online forums, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) techniques used to analyze forum data, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper addresses the need for future research to address open challenges, which could fall under cs.OH (Other Computer Science).
